  "notes": "Atikamekw (Atikamekw Nehiromowin) — Algonquian (Cree) language of Quebec, written in a Latin orthography (not syllabics, unlike most Cree varieties). ⟨c⟩ = /ʃ/ and ⟨tc⟩ = /tʃ/; ⟨r⟩ is a tap, the reflex of Proto-Algonquian *l which gives Atikamekw its 'r-dialect' character. Vowel length is written with a circumflex (â î ô) but is commonly left out in everyday writing; ⟨e⟩ is inherently long. The fortis/lenis consonant distinction is not written in standard spelling (an underline is used when precision is needed).",
